result.name: Lady M New York

reviews.text:
Lady M is a NYC based patisserie that famous for their Mille-crepe desserts. They have opened up quite a few branches here Hong Kong in the past couple of years including this branch at Festival Walk in Kowloon Tong. Opening hours are are 10am to 10pm daily. 

We visited this Lady M at Festival Walk recently and were quite impressed with both the signature Mille (HK$68 per slice) and the Pistachio Mille Crepe (HK$75 per slice). Both slices were delicately made and very tasty. These are soft slices made up of ultra thin crepes layered with flavoured pastry cream. They were both delicious and worth reordering. 

In the end, we really enjoyed our Mille-crepe slices at Lady M (Festival Walk) and will gladly return for another round in the future. These are a bit pricey but the quality is there. Lady M is worth trying if you run across one of their branches around Hong Kong.
I am not saying how good the cake is. You will know better than me. It is a nice place for resting after a long fight with the shop. A nice rest with a nice cake, perfect!!!

Not bad for this type of layer cake. Tried rose and green tea flavour. Green tea needs to more strong. Rose is distinctive and sweet. Taste of cream is strong and rich. Seating is comfortable on the sofa seats. Lucky enough to get one of the three tables with sofa seating inside as it was a weekday. I do have to say I am not a big fan of layer cake and will contribute to the low score. Lovers of this type of cake may love it.
Very tasty cakes!
Earl grey killing me!

reviews.text: Good arcade to shop for medium to medium-high end brands in a spacious environment with both restaurants and food court to suit varying tastes of customers. Great parking lot. Multiple sakes receipts accepted for free parking.

Very crowded and very clean like a hospital. Come here on Sunday and you can enjoy waiting for a table for an hour with everyone. Best place if you want to buy a Rolex for $900,000 to go with your yacht sitting in a port in Italy.
Multiple restaurants and shops. A very big mall, and a nice theater to watch movies. The restaurants were also very nice. A very good shopping mall overall.

I like Festival Walk as it is rarely super crowded like the malls at Sha Tin always seem to be. The TASTE supermarket is fantastic here with a range of products from around the world including Waitrose products and a good frozen section. Other stores I like here are Zara Home, Log On, M&S and the Cinema which let's you bring Starbucks in. I sometimes come here to walk around on rainy days too as it is so big and there are very few shoppers with suitcases.

I like Windows shopping here.cause if not people mountain people sea. Can very relaxed to take a look.some shop I used take a look.like hk a female designer. She design Chinese match west.she control color very. Very good. Also one best of world shoe shop. Tecstoni.name may be not correct. It is one of best Italian designer band shoe shop.
